The search dialog is provided by Fumadocs UI (`fumadocs-ui/components/dialog/search`). Our customization is via CSS overrides in `docs/app/global.css` lines 320-358.

Fumadocs-dev's search dialog (`packages/base-ui/src/components/dialog/search.tsx` line ~296) uses:
```
fixed left-1/2 top-4 md:top-[calc(50%-250px)] z-50 w-[calc(100%-1rem)] max-w-screen-sm -translate-x-1/2
```

Our docs site uses the Fumadocs default positioning which should already include these responsive styles. But we need to ensure:

1. In `docs/app/global.css`, add a mobile-specific rule to prevent iOS zoom on the search input:
```css
@media (max-width: 639px) {
  [role='dialog'] input[type='text'],
  [role='dialog'] input:not([type]) {
    font-size: 16px;
  }
}
```
This prevents Safari from zooming in when the search input is focused (Safari auto-zooms on inputs with font-size < 16px).

2. The existing CSS overrides at lines 469-488 already handle shadow reduction and tap targets for mobile. Verify they're working correctly.

3. Consider adding `overscroll-behavior: contain` to the search results list to prevent scroll chaining on mobile.

