These are global-level mobile improvements in `docs/app/global.css`.

Fumadocs-dev uses these patterns:
- Layout container: `min-h-(--fd-docs-height) [--fd-docs-height:100dvh]` (`packages/base-ui/src/layouts/docs/client.tsx` line 58)
- Layout container: `overflow-x-clip` to prevent horizontal scroll
- Sidebar viewport: `overscroll-contain` to prevent scroll chaining

The Fumadocs UI library that our docs uses likely already applies `--fd-docs-height: 100dvh` and `overflow-x-clip` via its layout components. But we should verify and reinforce:

1. Check if the docs layout already uses dvh. If not, add to `docs/app/global.css`:
```css
#nd-docs-layout {
  --fd-docs-height: 100dvh;
}
```
Note: This CSS variable is likely already set by Fumadocs since our docs uses fumadocs-ui@16.6.3 which includes these patterns. Only add if missing.

2. Add `overscroll-behavior-y: none` to body for docs pages to prevent accidental pull-to-refresh:
```css
@media (max-width: 767px) {
  body {
    overscroll-behavior-y: none;
  }
}
```
Only on mobile — desktop should allow normal overscroll behavior.

3. Add safe-area padding for the main content area on mobile:
```css
@media (max-width: 767px) {
  #nd-page {
    padding-left: max(1rem, env(safe-area-inset-left, 0px));
    padding-right: max(1rem, env(safe-area-inset-right, 0px));
  }
}
```
This ensures content doesn't get hidden behind notch/sensor housing on landscape mobile.

4. The `overflow-x-clip` is already set by Fumadocs on `#nd-docs-layout`. Verify this is present; if not, add it.

